===== RELEASE-GATE-RESULTS.md =====
# Farm Rx Release-Gate Results

**Current verdict:** NOT YET RELEASE-READY
**Reason:** All three local repair slices now pass focused root proof, including 26/26 browser tests. Fresh adversarial/cross-model review and the final full foundation/pre-commit gates remain; deployed non-production, physical-device, email, and push gates are not authorized or available.

## Green so far

- Baseline full local foundation gate.
- Live read-only service-role privilege disposition.
- Forward modern-PostgREST-claims repair with exact PostgreSQL 17 before/after proof.
- Forward scheduler/weather/per-device-push repair with pure regressions and fresh PostgreSQL 17 migration/RPC proof.
- Parent/isolated-frame CSP separation, revoked-farm recovery quarantine, raster PWA metadata, and safe-area behavior with strict regression plus Chromium desktop/phone proof.

## Still blocking release

- Fresh independent post-repair Sol/Terra/Luna review.
- Final full local foundation gate on the completed diff.
- No named non-production Supabase environment or scheduler secret set.
- No physical iOS/Android device and no authorized real email/push recipients.
- No commit approval.

No release gate will be marked green from historical evidence alone.

===== TERRA-WORKFLOW-REVIEW.md =====
## Terra Phase 1 reconnaissance report

1. Actual model and effort

Requested: `gpt-5.6-terra`, Medium.
Actual: GPT-5 Codex; this worker does not expose or permit verification of a pinned `gpt-5.6-terra` identity or reasoning-effort setting. I did not substitute or call another model.

2. Files read

- `docs/audits/2026-07-15-sol-foundation-review/NEXT-SESSION-SOL-TERRA-LUNA-LOOP.md`
- `CLAUDE.md`
- Audit roadmap, findings, proof-gap, and workflow-coverage documents.
- `vercel.json`, `vite.config.ts`, `index.html`, `package.json`, `playwright.config.ts`
- `public/market-quote-frame.html`
- `src/App.tsx`, `src/main.tsx`, `src/sw.ts`, `src/components/MarketQuote.tsx`
- Auth/offline paths: `src/auth/AuthProvider.tsx`, `RequireSession.tsx`, `farmContext.ts`, `src/data/workspaceCache.ts`, queue references, `src/lib/farmerErrors.ts`
- `src/styles/app.css`, `tests/e2e/foundation-shell.spec.ts`
- Existing `dist` PWA artifacts, read only.

Confirmed branch/commit: `codex/farmrx-release-gate-proof` is at `49614e75140fdf4dee94d916e32b386bef922f1a`, matching PR #1 head.

3. Commands/tool calls and failures

Read-only PowerShell inspection, `rg`, `git rev-parse/log/status/diff --check`, and the required `npx` prerequisite check ran. `npx` is available at `C:\Program Files\nodejs\npx.ps1`.

Failures:

- Combined discovery command: exit `1`; final `rg` path expression produced no match.
- Initial range-print command: PowerShell parser error: `Variable reference is not valid. ':' was not followed by a valid variable name character.` Corrected command succeeded.
- Git emitted warnings twice: `unable to access 'C:\Users\mason/.config/git/ignore': Permission denied`. Git state/proof commands still completed.

No deployment metadata or deployed response was queried: there is no approved preview URL or authorized test environment in scope.

4. Route, header, frame, PWA, and device workflow map

| Area | Actual implementation |
|---|---|
| Preview/CDN routes | Vercel rewrites extensionless paths to `/index.html`; assets and files with extensions remain static ([vercel.json](/C:/FarmRx/vercel.json:28)). |
| Client routes | `/login`; authenticated shell routes for Fields, Grain, Inventory, Profitability, Equipment, Tasks, Weather, Field Log, Scouting, Harvest, Programs, and Alerts; unknown routes redirect to `/fields` ([App.tsx](/C:/FarmRx/src/App.tsx:244)). |
| Header split | `/market-quote-frame.html` has a dedicated restrictive CSP; all other paths receive first-party CSP, anti-framing, nosniff, referrer, permission, and COOP headers ([vercel.json](/C:/FarmRx/vercel.json:6)). |
| TradingView | Grain creates six same-origin child frames with `sandbox="allow-scripts"` and `referrerPolicy="no-referrer"` ([MarketQuote.tsx](/C:/FarmRx/src/components/MarketQuote.tsx:16)). The frame only accepts six allow-listed symbols and loads TradingView’s bootstrap script ([market-quote-frame.html](/C:/FarmRx/public/market-quote-frame.html:11)). |
| PWA | Vite PWA injects a service worker with auto-update and standalone manifest ([vite.config.ts](/C:/FarmRx/vite.config.ts:8)); worker precaches the shell, immediately claims clients, and routes navigation to cached `/index.html` ([sw.ts](/C:/FarmRx/src/sw.ts:7)). |
| Offline data | Service worker caches the shell; farm data lives separately in user/farm-scoped IndexedDB and pending writes in local storage. Financial cache expires at 24 hours; operational cache at seven days ([workspaceCache.ts](/C:/FarmRx/src/data/workspaceCache.ts:1)). |
| Reconnect/retry | On reconnect, access is refreshed before queues replay; UI shows pending, sending, or “needs attention” plus “Try again” ([App.tsx](/C:/FarmRx/src/App.tsx:316)). |
| Conflict message | Stale writes are presented as: “This record changed in another tab or device. Reload before saving again.” ([farmerErrors.ts](/C:/FarmRx/src/lib/farmerErrors.ts:10)). |
| Mobile | Four primary destinations plus More; all other destinations are two taps away ([App.tsx](/C:/FarmRx/src/App.tsx:555)). CSS provides 60px bottom-nav targets and a 70px body reserve ([app.css](/C:/FarmRx/src/styles/app.css:533)). |

Skeptical-farmer path: login → choose farm if needed → work in Fields/Grain/etc. → receive clear offline/pending status → reconnect and replay → see blocked work as “Nothing was deleted” with retry → conflict asks for reload rather than silently overwriting. The known local browser suite covers this shell, offline field save/reopen, frame escape attempt, and mobile widths; it does not prove an installed physical device or deployed headers.

5. Findings / blockers

