## Terra serialized implementation slice — CSP, revoked-farm recovery, installed PWA polish (local only)

### Changed files

- `vercel.json` — parent CSP no longer permits TradingView in `img-src`, `connect-src`, or `frame-src`; the same-origin opaque frame remains the only permitted frame target. The frame's dedicated restrictive CSP still carries its narrowly required TradingView sources.
- `src/data/revokedFarmRecovery.ts` — versioned, project/user-scoped recovery vault; strict record validation; byte-for-byte write/read-back verification; revoked queue, needs-attention, and scouting-cleanup partition capture; no coordination leases; no replay API.
- `src/auth/farmContext.ts`, `src/data/workspaceCache.ts` — a live refresh quarantines work before clearing active bytes or publishing new access; cache deletion is verified after the transaction. A durable recovery failure fails closed.
- `src/components/RevokedFarmRecovery.tsx`, `src/App.tsx`, `src/styles/app.css` — plain-language inspect/export/explicit-dismiss surface available in the normal shell, farm chooser, and blocked-access screen. It has no retry/requeue control.
- `vite.config.ts`, `index.html`, `public/farm-rx-icon-192.png`, `public/farm-rx-icon-512.png`, `public/apple-touch-icon.png` — local raster manifest icons and Apple touch icon generated from the checked-in Farm Rx green Rx mark; standalone bottom navigation reserves exactly one safe-area inset.
- `src/data/revokedFarmRecovery.regression.ts`, `tests/e2e/foundation-shell.spec.ts`, `package.json` — deterministic recovery and CSP/PWA guard coverage.

### Before / after

Before: a revoked farm lost its IndexedDB workspace cache but retained local active queues and needs-attention entries, which could replay after a later re-grant. The parent CSP also directly permitted TradingView origins, and the PWA offered SVG only.

After: a successful live removal first moves every recognised current queue (Fields, field location/weather, Field Log, Scouting, Harvest, Inventory, Grain, Profitability, Equipment Tasks, Notifications, Programs), corresponding needs-attention records, and only the revoked farm's scouting-cleanup entries into a separately keyed recovery vault. The vault is read back before any active record is removed. It is not a queue and no code feeds it back into a queue; the farmer may export it or explicitly dismiss it. Caches are deleted and verified before the new access snapshot is persisted. Sign-out preserves recovery records while removing access state and workspace caches. Repeated handling deduplicates by original key/payload, other farms/users/projects remain isolated, and leases remain untouched.

### Exact local verification

Passed:

- `node_modules\\.bin\\tsx.cmd src/data/revokedFarmRecovery.regression.ts` — covers empty revoke, every current queue family, needs-attention capture, scouting partition, lease exclusion, write failure fail-closed behavior, repeat handling, re-grant-safe absence of an active queue, isolation, and explicit dismissal.
- `node_modules\\.bin\\tsc.cmd -b --force` — passed.
- `node_modules\\.bin\\vite.cmd build` — passed; generated manifest and service-worker build completed. Existing bundle-size advisory only.
- local static guard (Node) — passed: parsed `vercel.json`, rejects TradingView in parent `img-src`/`connect-src`/`frame-src`, requires parent `frame-src 'self'`, confirms the isolated frame's `default-src 'none'`, `frame-ancestors 'self'`, and TradingView bootstrap source; confirms built manifest raster icons and Apple touch icon.
- `git diff --check` — passed.

Browser proof attempt:

- Narrowed Playwright run for CSP, icon metadata, and mobile navigation was attempted. It stalled while Playwright's configured web-server invoked `npm run build`/`npm run preview`; the workstation's global npm/npx shim cannot read its global `npx-cli.js` path. The process was stopped without mutation. The same build passed through local `node_modules` binaries, and the static guard above passed, but no browser assertion is claimed for this slice.

### Residual limitations

- No deployed/CDN headers were inspected and no Vercel, Supabase, GitHub, database, provider, account, deployment, or production state was contacted.
- Installed iPhone/iPad safe-area, home-screen icon rendering, offline revoke/re-grant, and physical-device storage-pressure proof remain manual-device gates.
- The local recovery regression proves storage behavior with deterministic in-memory storage; a browser-level revoked-membership flow remains to be rerun once the local Playwright web-server shim is usable.

### Mutation statement

No staging, commit, push, deployment, live-data change, provider call, account use, or external mutation was performed. Pre-existing dirty worktree changes, including Sol's Edge/database work, were preserved.

